{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1770220214,"nonce":"sZuk7L88mVmSlFpv+7gFZnpWHKg=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87oSp69zwAAAAU_DhfX"},"added":["documentation"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1770220215,"nonce":"7FUYeaUHKMAcZ8mLJkY/Im73rT0=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87oSp69zwAAAAU_Dhgh"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1771596844,"nonce":"rqAOOa1hTOseDl/LCv5e00AIpF8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87qjKAU","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/162#issuecomment-3935084564"},"message":"## Additional scenario: working on an existing sub-PR created by another agent\n\nIssue #162 focuses on the \"create a new sub-issue branch from a parent PR\" flow. I hit a related but distinct scenario today that's worth capturing:\n\n**Scenario**: PR #238 (branch `copilot/sub-pr-233`, targeting `feature/issue-229`) had Copilot review comments that needed fixing. The branch already existed — I just needed to get into it, make edits, and push.\n\n### What worked\n\nThe existing `--branch` flag on `worktree_create.sh` handled this:\n```bash\nworktree_create.sh --issue 229 --type workspace --branch copilot/sub-pr-233\n```\n\n### Friction points\n\n1. **`--branch` flag is undocumented in CLAUDE.md** — The worktree section in CLAUDE.md doesn't mention it. I had to run `--help` to discover it existed. Adding it to the documented examples would help.\n\n2. **Issue number is awkward** — I used `--issue 229` (the parent issue), but my actual work was on PR #238's review comments. The worktree system is strictly issue-number-centric, but PR review work is PR-centric. There was no natural issue number to use.\n\n3. **Title verification was misleading** — `worktree_enter.sh` showed \"Sandboxed agent development: DevContainer with YOLO mode\" with the \"verify this matches your task\" warning. It didn't match — I was fixing push_gateway security review comments. Not blocking, but adds noise and could cause an overly-cautious agent to stop and ask the user.\n\n### Suggestions\n\n- **Document `--branch`** in CLAUDE.md's worktree section (low-hanging fruit, independent of #162's larger changes).\n- **Consider `--pr` flag** as an alternative to `--issue` — it could auto-detect the branch name and use the PR title for verification instead of the issue title.\n- **Soften the title verification** when `--branch` is explicitly provided — the user/agent already knows what branch they want; the mismatch warning is less useful in that case.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1771882667,"nonce":"ovLc5Quv7UDYMdSTBf4tYbA3zLg=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87rSZPG","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/162#issuecomment-3947467718"},"message":"## Emerging pattern: parent-issue branches\n\nWhile working on #249 (workspace rework), we arrived at a useful convention that extends a pattern already used by GitHub Copilot (branching from a PR branch to address review comments):\n\n**Pattern**: When an umbrella issue spawns sub-issues, the parent issue gets a long-lived branch (`feature/issue-\u003cN\u003e`). Sub-issue branches originate from the parent branch, and their PRs target the parent branch (not main). When the umbrella work is complete, the parent branch gets a final PR to main.\n\n**Benefits**:\n- Working artifacts (research docs, intent recovery files, etc.) accumulate on the parent branch where all sub-issue agents can access them\n- Artifacts with a limited lifespan can be removed before the final merge to main\n- The parent branch provides full context for any agent picking up a sub-task\n- PRs between sub-issues and the parent give the user visibility and control over merging\n\n**First use**: #249 → sub-issues #251, #252, plus a research branch from a Claude cloud session.\n\nThis is a workflow idea that emerged organically — not yet formalized into tooling or documentation.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}